[{"id":"1f22c67d34e6510e901c0448ece0246f","from":"Lesley Groff","from_email":"lesley@nysgllc.com","to":"J. Epstein","to_list":[{"name":"J. Epstein","email":"jeeproject@yahoo.com"}],"cc_list":[],"subject":"from Brad Grossman","date":"2008-04-22T12:35:34.000Z","formatted_date":"Apr 22, 2008","formatted_time":"12:35 PM","body":" \n\n \n\nFrom: Brad Grossman [mailto:grossman.brad@gmail.com] \nSent: Monday, April 21, 2008 4:52 PM\nTo: Lesley Groff\nSubject: Re: CHANGE OF ADDRESS for 11:45 Appt today\n\n \n\nDear Jeffrey,\n\n \n\nThank you for taking the time to meet with me.  Brockman, Ghislaine, and\nAdam Bly have been telling me about you for a while, and I was fortunate\nto see your passion for Science in person.\n\n \n\nI've been thinking about your project and our meeting, and I forgot to\ntell you about a guy  I met with -- Matthieu Ricard -- proclaimed the\nhappiest man in the world by University of Wisconsin Neuroscientist,\nRichard Davidson.  He radiated Brian's office weeks after Davidson's\nexperiments tested his neuroplasticity.   \n\n \n\nAnyway, enjoy Paris, and I hope to continue our conversation when you\nreturn.  I will be in NY until May 2nd, and then I will be back in LA\nfor a bit packing up for my move to NY.\n\n \n\nAll the best,\n\nBrad\n\n \n\n \n\nBrad Grossman\n\n(310) 614-4779\n\ngrossman.brad@gmail.com\n\n \n\nThis e-mail and any files transmitted with it are\n\nintended solely for the use of the individual or entity to whom they are\n\naddressed. If the reader of this e-mail is not the intended recipient or\n\nthe employee or agent responsible for delivering the message to the\n\nintended recipient, you are hereby notified that any use dissemination,\n\nforwarding, printing or copying of this e-mail is strictly prohibited.\n\nIf you have received this e-mail in error, please e-mail us at\n\n grossman.brad@gmail.com or call 310-614-4779\n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n\n\n\n\n \n\nOn Apr 21, 2008, at 5:16 AM, Lesley Groff wrote:\n\n\n\n\n\nAll Jeffrey 's  emails come to me and then I will get to Jeffrey.  So\nyou can send to me!\n\n \n\nTake care, Lesley\n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\nLesley Groff\n\nExecutive Assistant to Jeffrey Epstein\n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n________________________________\n\nFrom: Brad Grossman [mailto:grossman.brad@gmail.com] \nSent: Monday, April 21, 2008 12:09 AM\nTo: Lesley Groff\nSubject: Re: CHANGE OF ADDRESS for 11:45 Appt today\n\nLesley -- Thanks for facilitating the meeting.  Is there an email for\nJeffrey that I can contact him at?\n\nBrad Grossman\n\n(310) 614-4779\n\ngrossman.brad@gmail.com\n\n \n\nThis e-mail and any files transmitted with it are\n\nintended solely for the use of the individual or entity to whom they are\n\naddressed. If the reader of this e-mail is not the intended recipient or\n\nthe employee or agent responsible for delivering the message to the\n\nintended recipient, you are hereby notified that any use dissemination,\n\nforwarding, printing or copying of this e-mail is strictly prohibited.\n\nIf you have received this e-mail in error, please e-mail us at\n\n grossman.brad@gmail.com or call 310-614-4779\n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n\n\n\n\n \n\nOn Apr 17, 2008, at 6:14 AM, Lesley Groff wrote:\n\n\n\n\n\nThe address to Jeffrey's office is:\n\n457 Madison Ave, 4th Floor\n\nBetween 50th and 51st streets\n\nThanks!  LEsley\n\nFrom: Brad Grossman [mailto:grossman.brad@gmail.com] \nSent: Wednesday, April 16, 2008 6:34 PM\nTo: Lesley Groff\nSubject: Re: Jeffrey Epstein\n\n11:45 right?\n\nOn Apr 16, 2008, at 12:55 PM, Lesley Groff wrote:\n\n\n\n\n\n\nHello Brad.  The meeting at 11:30 tomorrow will be held at Jeffrey's\nhouse.  He lives at 9 East 71st Street between 5th and Madison.  I will\ncall you tomorrow to confirm.\n\nThanks,\n\nLesley Groff\n\nAssistant to Jeffrey Epstein\n\n\n\n\n\n\nBrad Grossman\n\n(310) 614-4779\n\ngrossman.brad@gmail.com <mailto:grossman.brad@gmail.com> \n\n \n\n \n\n","body_html":"<html xmlns:v=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:vml\" xmlns:o=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office\" xmlns:w=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:word\" xmlns:m=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/2004/12/omml\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40\">\n\n<head>\n<META HTTP-EQUIV=\"Content-Type\" CONTENT=\"text/html; charset=us-ascii\">\n<meta name=Generator content=\"Microsoft Word 12 (filtered medium)\">\n<!--[if !mso]>\n<style>\nv\\:* {behavior:url(#default#VML);}\no\\:* {behavior:url(#default#VML);}\nw\\:* {behavior:url(#default#VML);}\n.shape {behavior:url(#default#VML);}\n</style>\n<![endif]-->\n<style>\n<!--\n /* Font Definitions */\n @font-face\n\t{font-family:Helvetica;\n\tpanose-1:2 11 6 4 2 2 2 2 2 4;}\n@font-face\n\t{font-family:Helvetica;\n\tpanose-1:2 11 6 4 2 2 2 2 2 4;}\n@font-face\n\t{font-family:Calibri;\n\tpanose-1:2 15 5 2 2 2 4 3 2 4;}\n@font-face\n\t{font-family:Tahoma;\n\tpanose-1:2 11 6 4 3 5 4 4 2 4;}\n /* Style Definitions */\n p.MsoNormal, li.MsoNormal, div.MsoNormal\n\t{margin:0in;\n\tmargin-bottom:.0001pt;\n\tfont-size:12.0pt;\n\tfont-family:\"Times New Roman\",\"serif\";}\na:link, span.MsoHyperlink\n\t{mso-style-priority:99;\n\tcolor:blue;\n\ttext-decoration:underline;}\na:visited, span.MsoHyperlinkFollowed\n\t{mso-style-priority:99;\n\tcolor:purple;\n\ttext-decoration:underline;}\nspan.apple-style-span\n\t{mso-style-name:apple-style-span;}\nspan.EmailStyle18\n\t{mso-style-type:personal-reply;\n\tfont-family:\"Calibri\",\"sans-serif\";\n\tcolor:#1F497D;}\n.MsoChpDefault\n\t{mso-style-type:export-only;\n\tfont-size:10.0pt;}\n@page Section1\n\t{size:8.5in 11.0in;\n\tmargin:1.0in 1.0in 1.0in 1.0in;}\ndiv.Section1\n\t{page:Section1;}\n-->\n</style>\n<!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\n <o:shapedefaults v:ext=\"edit\" spidmax=\"1026\" />\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\n <o:shapelayout v:ext=\"edit\">\n  <o:idmap v:ext=\"edit\" data=\"1\" />\n </o:shapelayout></xml><![endif]-->\n</head>\n\n<body lang=EN-US link=blue vlink=purple style='word-wrap: break-word;\n-khtml-nbsp-mode: space;-khtml-line-break: after-white-space'>\n\n<div class=Section1>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal><span style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\"Calibri\",\"sans-serif\";\ncolor:#1F497D'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal><span style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\"Calibri\",\"sans-serif\";\ncolor:#1F497D'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\n\n<div>\n\n<div style='border:none;border-top:solid #B5C4DF 1.0pt;padding:3.0pt 0in 0in 0in'>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal><b><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\"Tahoma\",\"sans-serif\"'>From:</span></b><span\nstyle='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\"Tahoma\",\"sans-serif\"'> Brad Grossman\n[mailto:grossman.brad@gmail.com] <br>\n<b>Sent:</b> Monday, April 21, 2008 4:52 PM<br>\n<b>To:</b> Lesley Groff<br>\n<b>Subject:</b> Re: CHANGE OF ADDRESS for 11:45 Appt today<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n</div>\n\n</div>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal>Dear Jeffrey,<o:p></o:p></p>\n\n<div>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>\n\n</div>\n\n<div>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal>Thank you for taking the time to meet with me.&nbsp;\nBrockman, Ghislaine, and Adam Bly have been telling me about you for a while,\nand I was fortunate to see your passion for Science in person.<o:p></o:p></p>\n\n</div>\n\n<div>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>\n\n</div>\n\n<div>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal>I've been thinking about your project and our meeting, and I\nforgot to tell you about a guy&nbsp; I met with -- Matthieu Ricard --\nproclaimed the happiest man in the world by University of Wisconsin\nNeuroscientist, Richard Davidson.&nbsp; He radiated Brian's office weeks after\nDavidson's experiments tested his neuroplasticity.&nbsp; &nbsp;<o:p></o:p></p>\n\n</div>\n\n<div>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>\n\n</div>\n\n<div>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal>Anyway, enjoy Paris, and I hope to continue our conversation\nwhen you return.&nbsp; I will be in NY until May 2nd, and then I will be back\nin LA for a bit packing up for my move to NY.<o:p></o:p></p>\n\n</div>\n\n<div>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>\n\n</div>\n\n<div>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal>All the best,<o:p></o:p></p>\n\n</div>\n\n<div>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal>Brad<o:p></o:p></p>\n\n</div>\n\n<div>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>\n\n</div>\n\n<div>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>\n\n<div>\n\n<div>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal><span style='font-size:9.0pt;font-family:\"Helvetica\",\"sans-serif\";\ncolor:black'>Brad Grossman<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n</div>\n\n<div>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal><span style='font-size:9.0pt;font-family:\"Helvetica\",\"sans-serif\";\ncolor:black'>(310) 614-4779<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n</div>\n\n<div>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal><span style='font-size:9.0pt;font-family:\"Helvetica\",\"sans-serif\";\ncolor:black'><a href=\"mailto:grossman.brad@gmail.com\">grossman.brad@gmail.com</a><o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n</div>\n\n<div>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal><span style='font-size:9.0pt;font-family:\"Helvetica\",\"sans-serif\";\ncolor:black'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\n\n</div>\n\n<div>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal><span class=apple-style-span><span style='font-size:9.0pt;\nfont-family:\"Helvetica\",\"sans-serif\";color:#0016D4'>This e-mail and any files\ntransmitted with it are</span></span><span style='font-size:9.0pt;font-family:\n\"Helvetica\",\"sans-serif\";color:black'><o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n</div>\n\n<div>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal><span class=apple-style-span><span style='font-size:9.0pt;\nfont-family:\"Helvetica\",\"sans-serif\";color:#0016D4'>intended solely for the use\nof the individual or entity to whom they are</span></span><span\nstyle='font-size:9.0pt;font-family:\"Helvetica\",\"sans-serif\";color:black'><o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n</div>\n\n<div>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal><span class=apple-style-span><span style='font-size:9.0pt;\nfont-family:\"Helvetica\",\"sans-serif\";color:#0016D4'>addressed. If the reader of\nthis e-mail is not the intended recipient or</span></span><span\nstyle='font-size:9.0pt;font-family:\"Helvetica\",\"sans-serif\"